issues.title: Incorrectly injecting the version into projen
issues.body:
I noticed that the version of `cdktf-provider-project` that is used by `package.json` is an [old version](https://github.com/cdktf/cdktf-provider-github/blob/main/package.json#L46) and does not match the [locked version](https://github.com/cdktf/cdktf-provider-github/blob/main/yarn.lock#L104). This has been fine, because [the semver constraint allows it](https://jubianchi.github.io/semver-check/#/^0.2.8/0.2.65), but it will cause a problem when either the [major](https://jubianchi.github.io/semver-check/#/^0.2.8/1.0.0) or [minor](https://jubianchi.github.io/semver-check/#/^0.2.8/0.3.0) version of this project gets bumped.

This happens because the [project generator loads from](https://github.com/cdktf/cdktf-provider-project/blob/main/src/index.ts#L14) `version.json`, which was correct until projen [updated the bump task](https://github.com/cdktf/cdktf-provider-project/blob/main/.projen/tasks.json#L31) to instead write the version into `package.json` and abandoned `version.json`.

issues.title: Properly render large documentation files
issues.body:
Hello!

Right now Markdown wiki for aws cdktf provider is too big to render in Github (about 35 megabytes):
https://github.com/hashicorp/cdktf-provider-aws/blob/main/API.md

One possible way to work around it is to create Github Wiki instead of single markdown file (I am not sure, if it will help). Another option is to generate something like a documentation site (like this: https://docs.aws.amazon.com/cdk/api/v2/docs/aws-construct-library.html) and host it on Github Pages.

issues.title: Allow usage for private repositories
issues.body:
Any plans on allowing to use this projen template for private repository usage? We require some providers to be available as library in order to reference them in other jsii libraries.

If yes I'd go ahead, fork this and allow to override/configure the currently hardcoded values.
